To measure the capacitance of the sensor, you can use the RC circuit to generate an exponential charge and discharge curve. Measure the time it takes to charge the capacitor until it reaches a threshold voltage (63.2% of Vcc). Capacitance (C) can be calculated using the following formula:

```
C = T / R
